<rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>NYT &gt; Technology</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/section/technology</link><description>Technology industry news, commentary, and analysis, with reporting on big tech, startups, and internet culture. The New York Times is a hub for conversation about news and ideas.</description><atom:link rel="self" href="https://rss.nytimes.com/services/xml/rss/nyt/Technology.xml" type="application/rss+xml" /><item><title>The Yoto Music Box Is a Ray of Hope Amid the ‘Techlash’</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/07/01/technology/personaltech/yoto-music-box-screens.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/07/01/technology/personaltech/yoto-music-box-screens.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</guid><atom:link rel="standout" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2026/07/01/technology/personaltech/yoto-music-box-screens.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss" /><description>Amid widespread “techlash” over addictive screens and apps, the Yoto, an audio player for children, shows there’s still a way to make money while doing something nice.</description><dc:creator>Brian X. Chen and Sam Bush</dc:creator><pubDate>Wed, 01 Jul 2026 09:01:48 GMT</pubDate><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Children</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Electronics</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Audio Recordings</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Downloads and Streaming</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Music</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Yoto</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">The Beatles</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">internal-open-access-from-nl</category><media:content url="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2026/06/23/23visualUploader-33452-cover/23visualUploader-33452-cover-videoSixteenByNineJumbo1600-v2.jpg" medium="image" /></item><item><title>Apple Sues OpenAI, Accusing It of Stealing Company Secrets</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/07/10/technology/apple-openai-lawsuit.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/07/10/technology/apple-openai-lawsuit.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</guid><atom:link rel="standout" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2026/07/10/technology/apple-openai-lawsuit.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss" /><description>The two companies struck a deal in 2024 to offer A.I. services on Apple devices, but their partnership has soured.</description><dc:creator>Kalley Huang and Cade Metz</dc:creator><pubDate>Fri, 10 Jul 2026 21:08:14 GMT</pubDate><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Intellectual property</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Corporate espionage</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Apple</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">OpenAI</category><media:content url="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2026/07/10/multimedia/10biz-apple-openai2-tlmg/10biz-apple-openai2-tlmg-videoSixteenByNineJumbo1600.jpg" medium="image"><media:credit>Karsten Moran for The New York Times</media:credit><media:description>Apple made several accusations against OpenAI in its lawsuit, including that OpenAI had asked job candidates from Apple to share details about secret projects.</media:description></media:content></item><item><title>OpenAI Releases GPT-5.6 Sol, Its Most Powerful AI Model Yet</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/07/09/technology/openai-sol-ai.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/07/09/technology/openai-sol-ai.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</guid><atom:link rel="standout" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2026/07/09/technology/openai-sol-ai.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss" /><description>The new release was delayed after the U.S. government restricted the latest artificial intelligence models over cybersecurity concerns.</description><dc:creator>Cade Metz</dc:creator><pubDate>Thu, 09 Jul 2026 19:30:19 GMT</pubDate><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">OpenAI</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Artificial intelligence</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Regulation and Deregulation</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Computers and the Internet</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Tech Industry</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Anthropic</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Computer security</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Public-Private Partnerships</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">US Politics</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Donald Trump</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Executive Orders</category><media:content url="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2026/07/09/multimedia/OPENAI-SOL-1-tghz/OPENAI-SOL-1-tghz-videoSixteenByNineJumbo1600.jpg" medium="image"><media:credit>Hiroko Masuike/The New York Times</media:credit><media:description>OpenAI also unveiled a new tool on Thursday, called ChatGPT Work, which is powered by GPT-5.6 Sol. </media:description></media:content></item></channel></rss>